<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Apical half of wings black, fore wing with yellow spot at marginal cell; two bullae of vein 
<number box="[1290,1304,828,852]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
<emphasis box="[1303,1355,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">rs-m</emphasis>
of fore wing well separated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,900,925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Description</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[359,465,900,925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Holotype</typeStatus>
female). Head. Antenna with 
<number box="[837,865,900,924]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="28.0">28</number>
flagellomeres, first flagellomere 
<number box="[1266,1300,900,925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x length of second; frons concave and polished medially, punctate laterally, carina between antennal sockets extending to upper margin of face; face 
<number box="[480,529,972,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.55">0.55</number>
x as high as wide, medially raised with dense striations, laterally with large punctures, pubescent; clypeus coarsely punctate, about 
<number box="[800,835,1008,1032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.4">0.4</number>
x as high as wide, with small vertical ridge apicomedially; labrum 
<number box="[356,391,1044,1068]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.9">0.9</number>
x as long as its basal width; malar space equal to basal width of mandible; lower tooth of mandible longer than upper tooth, inner margins of eyes divergent ventrally; diameter of lateral ocellus 
<number box="[1387,1422,1079,1104]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.6">0.6</number>
x ocellar-ocular distance; vertex with sparse punctures; occipital carina ventrally meeting hypostomal carina about 
<number box="[151,186,1152,1176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.7">0.7</number>
x basal mandible width from base of mandible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
Mesosoma. Epomia absent; pronotum subpolished, with some small striations at ventral corner, posterior corner densely punctate; mesoscutum 
<number box="[596,631,1224,1248]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.9">0.9</number>
x as long as wide at anterior level of tegulae, with dense punctures, pubescent, notauli strong; scutellum convex, densely punctate, pubescent, lateral carina present basally; postscutellum polished, impunctate; mesopleuron densely punctate, dorsally striate-punctate, pubescent except medially, epicnemial carina angled medially, extending to subalar prominence; sternaulus weakly indicated anteriorly; mesosternum densely punctate, posterior transverse carina present medially; metapleuron densely, finely punctate, pubescent, submetapleural carina complete; propodeum with some small wrinkles above posterior transverse carina; outer side of apical margin of fore tibia forming small thorn, fore basitarsus 
<number box="[1296,1331,1440,1464]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="3.3">3.3</number>
x second tarsomere; mid basitarsus 
<date box="[446,474,1476,1500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<number box="[446,459,1476,1500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
second tarsomere; hind leg with femur 
<number box="[926,961,1476,1500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="3.4">3.4</number>
x as long as wide, length 
<number box="[1250,1285,1476,1500]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.7">0.7</number>
x tibia, tarsus 
<number box="[151,186,1512,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.9">0.9</number>
x tibia length, basitarsus 
<number box="[472,507,1511,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.5">2.5</number>
x second tarsomere, fifth tarsomere 
<number box="[919,954,1512,1536]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.1">2.1</number>
x longer than third. Fore wing length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="12.7">12.7 mm</quantity>
, areolet absent, vein 
<emphasis box="[436,464,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Rs</emphasis>
&amp; 
<emphasis box="[486,509,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">M</emphasis>
slightly distad of 
<emphasis box="[715,765,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">cu-a</emphasis>
, vein 
<number box="[836,850,1548,1572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
<emphasis box="[850,901,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">rs-m</emphasis>
about 
<number box="[980,1014,1548,1573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="1.5">1.5</number>
x distance between 
<number box="[1238,1252,1548,1572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
<emphasis box="[1251,1302,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">rs-m</emphasis>
and 
<number box="[1359,1373,1548,1572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
<emphasis box="[1373,1429,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">m-cu</emphasis>
, hind wing with first abscissa of vein 
<emphasis box="[564,597,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Cu</emphasis>
<number box="[596,610,1584,1608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[686,721,1584,1608]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.8">0.8</number>
x length of vein 
<emphasis box="[905,955,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">cu-a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
Metasoma. Tergites polished with sparse, small punctures; first tergite 
<number box="[1008,1043,1620,1644]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.2">2.2</number>
x as long as apical width, sparsely punctate medially, lateral longitudinal carina well developed basally; second tergite 
<number box="[1110,1159,1655,1680]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="0.45">0.45</number>
x as long as first tergite, 
<number box="[151,200,1692,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="1.25">1.25</number>
x longer than third; first sternite with low, round swelling; ovipositor compressed, length from base of subgenital plate about 
<number box="[407,442,1728,1752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="1.4">1.4</number>
x as long as hind tibia, with small teeth apically of both valves, subgenital plate 
<number box="[1356,1391,1727,1752]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.5">2.5</number>
x as long as second tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
Colour. Reddish. Antenna brown, but scape and pedicel reddish ventrally; hind tibia and tarsus blackish, apical half of wings infuscate, marginal cell with yellow spot in infuscate area (
<figureCitation box="[967,1035,1836,1861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1922,1944]" captionTargetBox="[292,1299,826,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[292,1300,823,1867]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wings: a. Phalgea lutea (holotype); b. Phalgea maculata sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233467/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
Fig. 
<number box="[1019,1035,1836,1860]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" box="[199,389,1871,1896]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,828,2005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1908,1933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Comparison.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang" authorityName="Wang" box="[677,965,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Phalgea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melaptera">
<emphasis box="[677,892,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">Phalgea melaptera</emphasis>
Wang
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance. It differs from the latter by the presence of a yellowish spot at the marginal cell of the fore wing and the two bullae on vein 
<number box="[1336,1349,1944,1968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
<emphasis box="[1349,1406,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">m-cu</emphasis>
of the fore wing are well separated, distinctly further apart than in 
<taxonomicName box="[864,1006,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Phalgea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melaptera">
<emphasis box="[864,1006,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="147">P. melaptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,988,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,320]" box="[199,988,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently known only from Khoang Xanh (Hanoi City).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this species refers to the spot at the marginal cell of the fore wing. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="148">Ecology.</emphasis>
The single specimen was collected in secondary forest near a stream. 
